## Known Issues / Next Session

### Bulk Ingest — Case Boundary Merging
When `bulk_ingest.py` was run, corrupted OCR headers caused the case boundary regex to merge consecutive cases into a single oversized block. The `Duration/Investigation` discriminator is not reliable at scale across all 309 cases.

**Plan for next session:**
1. Build an OCR header repair script using `pdfplumber` with coordinate-aware extraction to get cleaner header text directly from the PDF
2. Use the LLM to identify and normalize case boundaries from the PDF-extracted headers
3. Generate a structured `{case_number, start_page, end_page}` index
4. Replace the fragile regex in `bulk_ingest.py` with a lookup into this index

This will make `bulk_ingest.py` reliable and also make future re-runs faster.
